main event: Seven white lights were observed in the sky near Waynesboro, Pennsylvania on September 20, 1968.
interesting points: The lights were about the size of jet aircraft and were observed at a 20-degree elevation., They traveled from southeast to northwest and disappeared over the horizon in 10-15 minutes., The observer reported no noise and no visible vapor trails., The observer concluded they were not high-flying aircraft due to the lack of disturbance., The observation lasted for about 10-15 minutes.
sighted object: seven white lights in the sky
witness description: Civilian observer at Ft. Detrick, Md.
